PROJECT WORKFLOW – MEDTRACK AWS CLOUD-ENABLED HEALTHCARE MANAGEMENT SYSTEM

1. Backend Development and Application Setup
   - Develop the backend using Flask.
   - Create routes for user registration, login, and book request.
   - Integrate AWS services using boto3 for communication with cloud resources.

2. AWS Account Setup and Login
   - Create an AWS account if not already available.
   - Log in to the AWS Management Console.
   - Prepare the environment for using AWS services.

3. DynamoDB Database Creation and Setup
   - Create a DynamoDB table to store application data.
   - Configure attributes for user information and book request details.
   - Connect the Flask backend to DynamoDB for storing and retrieving data.

4. SNS Notification Setup
   - Create an Amazon SNS topic for notifications.
   - Configure SNS to send notifications when a book request is submitted.
   - Subscribe users and staff emails to receive notifications.

5. IAM Role Setup
   - Create an IAM role for secure access between services.
   - Attach required policies for DynamoDB, SNS, and EC2.
   - Assign the IAM role to the EC2 instance.

6. EC2 Instance Setup
   - Launch an EC2 instance to host the Flask web application.
   - Configure security groups to allow HTTP (port 80) and SSH (port 22).
   - Install Python, Flask, and required libraries.

7. Deployment on EC2
   - Upload the Flask project files to the EC2 instance.
   - Install dependencies using pip.
   - Run the Flask application on the server.

8. Testing and Deployment
   - Test user registration functionality.
   - Test login system.
   - Test book request submission.
   - Verify SNS email notifications are received.
   - Ensure the application works correctly after deployment.
